Hey, did you know that when a person dies, the matters they left unresolved keep living on, like an echo? When the soul learns to accept them, it can finally move on. But you’ve held on for such a long time. Could it be… are you afraid of dying?

Value.Text: You are dead, Thane. You’re inside my mind, my world, except everything you saw was made by you.

Value.Text: I gave you what you wanted. Why are you still unhappy? You should be able to admit your mistakes now.

Value.Text: I see. You’re right, despite of my appearance, I am not the one because of whom you ended up here. I am here to guide you, to help you resolve your thoughts and move on. I go by many names, but the one you’d know me by is the Grim Reaper.
Value.ResponseText: Are you going to continue ignoring my questions? I might… have made mistakes, I might have hurt others, but do I not deserve to know? Despite all, I have always done my best, but I am human, I am not perfect. You can’t condemn me for being flawed, because my flaws make me human.

Value.Text: You think this must be a dream, right? You can call it a dream if you want. But don’t keep your eyes closed for too long. Reality might leave you behind
